Hello lovelies, recently my skin felt dull, I could see a lot of white & black heads. Skin was definitely not looking even. So I decided to show some skin love! 🔊sound on.

Got an opportunity to try the skin services at Dr Jamuna Pai’s SkinLab located at panampally nagar Kochi. 

The doctor suggested to do a “Hydra Pure pore facial” which helps with tackling acne, aiding glow to the skin, it also helps with hydration. The whole session was comfortable and quite relaxing. I started to see the glow the next day and as the days passed my skin looked way better and healthier. 

If you guys are based in Kochi, do check out dr Jamuna Pai s skin lab for some amazing skin.

Hello lovelies,

Sound on 🔉 
I got my hands on the CITTA pure rose water mist. The brand gave me opportunity to try it. Now I was using this for weeks and I can gladly say that my skin was beginning to look healthier with a happy glow. 

I have inserted shots from day 1,4,9 & 16. The mist is very calming so it’s good for sensitive skin. My skin felt refreshed and pores looked tightened upon use. Initially when I started using this toner I just got out of my antibiotics and then came onto my periods so my skin was all over the place. Gradually with usage of this toner my skin felt or healed better. My mild breakouts started fading and texture seemed getting better. 

Back in the days you could say rose water toners were my very first step in my skincare routine. I used to use the ones by kama & forest essentials but it’s expensive. So if you are on the lookout for an alternative give this a try. It’s easy to spritz, very light weight and you can’t go wrong with this toner. 

INR 575 for 100ml

Features/benefits:
•dermatologist tested & approved
•tones effectively 
•stimulate collagen production 
•prevents acne & pigmentation 
•suitable for all genders and skin types 

Link in bio if you guys want to check out the product or you can even browse through their site to see other products they have.

Hello lovelies,
Recently I got my hands on the Swiss beauty more than glitter lipstick in the shade glimmer coral. 
First off the packaging is stunning, it’s where you click from the top and the bullet part drops. Applies like butter, and yes this is highly metallic. If you know the 90’s era where most women used to use metallic lipsticks or glosses, this reminded me of that. 
The shade glimmer coral is a coral shade with red undertones & gold shimmers which is finely milled. This is not for the faint of heart lol but I like metallic lipsticks, I usually apply it as lip topper and you get a good shade. 
If you like metallic lipsticks then you can give this a shot. 
INR 449/

Hello lovelies,
Got my hands on the viral loreal infallible tinted serum foundation, this is in the shade medium 4-5. This range offers very few shades only here which is a bummer. The shade medium matches pretty fine. Once it sets it’s like my exact shade. 
The first time I applied this I noticed it blended really well but started peeling around my lower cheeks and it didn’t sit well on the skin but that could be due to the sunscreen or something else. This happened when I applied a second layer of the foundation so I am not sure what the cause was.

However after few days I tried this again and it was flawless. Lately I have been reaching out to this more often. It’s light weight and looks natural with a medium coverage finish. Lasts long but after a few hours when I get oily I could see a slight transfer with the foundation which is normal as I do live in a humid climate. But overall it’s a good foundation. 

Have you guys tried this?💖

I recently received these blushes and other chrome eyeliners in #pr and wanted to swatch the blushes for you guys. These are from @parulgargbeauty
 
The packaging is stunning, it also includes a sponge tip sort of applicator to blend the blush. However I prefer using a brush for faster application. The finish is like a satin matte but upon setting it with powder it becomes matte.
